    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-21T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-21T12:00:00-05:00" n="712"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11564.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">O’Shaughnessy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-21T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1914, 12 m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>768. Say to General Huerta that we are informed that his forces contemplate
                    destruction of railroads from Vera Cruz. We hope that this is not true. As the
                    roads to Vera Cruz are the outlet for foreigners in the interior this Government
                    might feel it its duty to take <pb facs="0595" n="479" xml:id="pg_479"/> means
                    to prevent interruption of railroad communication between the capital and the
                    seacoast.</p>
                <p>While there is no excitement here and no apparent danger to Mexican
                    representative we will as a precaution furnish a guard to Mexican Embassy
                    here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
